The following code seems to crash the compiler:
```scala
class A(s: String) {
  def foo(x: A) = x
	
  def test {
    val a = Array[A]()
    for (i <- 0 to 0) {
      a(i) = a(i).foo(new A(i))
    }
  }
}
```
with the error:
`Error in Scala compiler: symbol value <error> does not exist in A$$anonfun$test$1.apply$mcVI$sp`
